

A simple web app to track compliance tasks across multiple clients. Built as part of an assignment for LedgersCFO.

---

App: https://your-frontend.vercel.app
API: https://your-backend.vercel.app/api


https://github.com/Harsha872/mini-compliance-tracker


At LedgersCFO, teams handle compliance work for multiple clients — filings, audits, certifications and so on. This app gives a simple interface to manage all of that in one place.

- View all clients in a sidebar
- Click a client to see their tasks
- Add new tasks with title, description, category, due date and priority
- Mark tasks as completed or revert them back to pending
- Filter tasks by status or category
- Search tasks by title, description or category
- Search clients by name or industry
- Overdue tasks (past due date, still pending) are highlighted in red automatically
- Summary stats show total, pending and completed count per client
- Add new clients directly from the sidebar


methods used API Endpoints are
GET - get all clients
POST - Add a new client
GET - Get tasks for a client
POST - create a new task
PUT - Toggle task status

git clone https://github.com/Harsha872/mini-compliance-tracker.git
cd mini-compliance-tracker

Tradeoffs

- Filtering and search happen on the frontend rather than server side. This is fine for small datasets per client but would need to move to API query params at scale.
- No authentication. Assumed out of scope for this assignment. In a real product every route would be behind auth.
- Used MongoDB over a relational DB. Faster to set up and flexible for this use case. A relational DB would make more sense if relationships between entities become more complex.
- State is managed with React hooks only. No Redux or Zustand. Sufficient for this scope.

Assumptions

- A single user manages all clients. No multi-user or role-based access needed.
- A task belongs to exactly one client and cannot be reassigned.
- Overdue means the due date is in the past and status is still Pending. Completed tasks are never overdue.
- Priority is set at task creation and does not change. Only status is toggled after creation.
- Seed data is included so the app is usable immediately without manual data entry.

